President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Jose W. Fernandez for multiple positions, including Under Secretary of State (Economic Growth, Energy and the Environment). Fernandez is currently a partner at Gibson Dunn & Crutcher LLP in New York and has previously served as Assistant Secretary of State for Economic, Energy and Business Affairs. He has been recognized for his accomplishments in the private sector and is involved in various civic activities. Fernandez holds a Bachelor's Degree from Dartmouth College and a J.D. from Columbia University. He is fluent in Spanish, Portuguese, and French.